mation about the proportion of positive results for random mandatory drugs tests can be found by selecting table 7.4 in the ‘Chapter 7 tables – Random mandatory drug testing’ link’.</p><p> </p><p>Further information about the number of incidents where drugs were found can be found by selecting table 9.2 in the ‘Chapter 9 tables – Finds in prison’ link.</p><p> </p><p>These prisons are also part of the 10 Prisons Project which aims to reduce violence in 10 of our most challenging prisons by reducing the supply of drugs; restoring basic decency and providing the training and support for prison officers to challenge the behaviour that drives violence. The project received an initial £10 million funding to improve security and decency, and bolster leadership capability over a 12-month period.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland","257409 ; 257410 ; 257629 ; 257630 ; 258895 ; 258896 ; 258899 ; 258900 ; 258906 ; 258907 ; 258913 ; 258920 ; 258921 ; 258922 ; 258923 ; 258930 ; 258931 ; 258932 ; 258933","2019-06-17T16:45:00.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128983/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128983/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128983/answer","South Swindon","Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128983/answer/previousversion/122065","Biography information for Robert Buckland","54","Justice","Justice","2019-06-03","Moorland Prison: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many incidents there have been where drugs were found at HMP Moorland in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Duncan Smith","Chingford and Woodford Green","Mr Iain Duncan Smith","258914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128984","Department for Transport","false","2019-06-11","<p>The Government’s 2018 cycling and walking safety review considered this matter carefully. The Government’s response to the safety review, published in November 2018, summarises the arguments for and against making helmets compulsory, and explains the Government’s position. In short, the Government will continue to encourage cyclists to wear helmets, but believes that this should remain a matter of individual choice. The Government has committed to undertake three actions over the next two years as part of its cycling and walking safety action plan. First, it will continue to promote and encourage cyclists to wear helmets, especially children. Secondly, the Government will provide strengthened advice on fitting of cycle helmets for children, as part of wider advice on use of safety equipment and attire when cycling. Thirdly, the Government will review evidence and international experience on mandatory helmets for children and provide clear guidance to help parents choose what is appropriate for their child.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2019-06-11T15:41:16.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128984/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128984/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128984/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-06-03","Cycling: Helmets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of making the wearing of helmets compulsory for cyclists.","false","Biography information for Faisal Rashid","Warrington South","Faisal Rashid","259450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128985","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-06-10","<p>Kent, Surrey &amp; Sussex CRC, operated by Seetec, was selected as the preferred provider of probation services in the South West and Wales following a competitive process involving the evaluation of bids against a range of factors including in relation to the quality of service delivery and value for money.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2019-06-10T14:55:22.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128985/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128985/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128985/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-06-03","Seetec: Probation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment his Department made of the business proposal put forward by Seetec to manage probation services in South West England and Wales following the collapse of the previous provider, Working Links; and whether that proposal was evaluated against a public sector bid.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","259131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128986","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-06-11","<p>Latest figures on the number working days lost due to sickness and sickness absence rates in the National Probation Service can be found in table 17 in the HMPPS Workforce Statistics Bulletin at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/801838/hr-publication-tables-march-2019.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/801838/hr-publication-tables-march-2019.xlsx</a></p><p>HMPPS is committed to ensuring the health, safety and wellbeing of its staff in England and Wales, with all staff having access to a comprehensive occupational health service and employee assistance programme.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2019-06-11T13:04:25.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128986/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128986/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128986/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-06-03","National Probation Service for England and Wales: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the average sickness rate is for employees of the National Probation Service.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","259132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128987","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-06-10","<p>This information is included as part of quarterly re-offending statistics, and can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/payment-by-results-statistics</p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2019-06-10T15:00:26.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128987/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128987/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128987/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-06-03","Reoffenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the re-offending rates were of prisoners supervised by the National Probation Service in each year since 2015 for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","259133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128988","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-06-11","<p>The total amount spent by the Ministry of Justice on the National Probation Service for the years requested is set out in a summary table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Years</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Probation Expenditure, nominal</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2018/19</p></td><td><p>£507,600,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>£441,900,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>£456,100,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>£440,000,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>£364,200,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Please note:</strong></p><p>Figures have been rounded and show actual costs <br> The 2018/19 data is finalised but subject to audit</p><p>Responsibility for providing probation services transferred to the new National Probation Service part way through the financial year 2014/15</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2019-06-11T13:00:56.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128988/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128988/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1128988/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-06-03","National Probation Service for England and Wales: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the cost of the National Probation Service has been in each year since 2015.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","259134"
